block content
  p Now we can install Homebrew, the package manager for Macs.
  
  p Copy and paste this line into your terminal and press Enter.
  
  p.pretty /usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"

  p Again, don't worry if you don't understand the line above - you don't need to. The point is it installs Homebrew. Developers just copy and paste these things from the internet too.
